cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a framework for simultaneous feature learning and subspace clustering for visual data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a Convolutional Neural Network (ConvNet) for feature learning, which is a popular tool in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a dual self-supervision technique, which involves spectral clustering, a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed approach on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
